spanGrp.span: Yís antepasado-wa rö estee ji cabécar
these are their dresses… my ancestors uh… they used to live uh… they used to kill everything and saved the skin;
(_) je rö jie-wa detsí (_) yís antepasado-wa rö esteee jie-wa sẽr-gẽ rö mãĩ esteee jie-wa të kable jirö jirö kte-gẽ je kable je rö jirö kulítö' ble-gẽ rö
they were clean, not like now that we kill [animals] and throw everything in the yard, on the ground.
je rö sikinã ka rö (_) ka rö ji se datsẽ-ra je kablé të esteee jirö ktá je je tule-gẽ rö jũĩtö inga jĩshugö inga
It is not… they used to save everything in tree holes uh… in bags or something like that.
Ka rö (_) jie-wa të kable (_) ble-gẽ rö kal jenẽi nã estee bolsa jãrga jirö bi je bi
It was not like now uh… the new generations;
Ka rö ji sa datsẽ-ra esteee ji nuevo-wa datsẽ-ra
they do not save them like that;
instead they throw everything here and there.
Je kable je tule-gẽ rö jamĩwa_jiwa jamĩwa_jiwa
What they save is no longer clean;
they say that everything they save is clean.
kable jirö ble-gẽ jie-wa të ra je rö (_) siginã she í të
